-- Former Itaú banker to become Latam CFO for HSBC -source
-- By Aluisio Pereira and Guillermo Parra-Bernal
-- Fri Jul 04, 2014 12:39PM EDT
-- None



SAO PAULO, July 4 (Reuters) - Rogério Calderón, a former senior executive at Brazilian bank Itaú, has been tapped to become chief financial officer of HSBC <HSBA.L> in Latin America, according to a source with knowledge of the appointment.

Until April, Calderón, previously a PricewaterhouseCoopers executive, was senior vice president of finance risk and compliance at Itaú Unibanco Holding SA <ITUB4.SA>, Brazil's largest non-government bank.